                    <row>
                        <cell rend="tdLeft">being unable</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdCom"/>
                        <cell rend="tdCentre">We cannot pay the rent.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdRight">
                            <hi rend="red">mā-ngiddū</hi>-š ǝnxaḷḷṣu l-ǝkrē.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdID">Wir können die Miete nicht zahlen.</cell>
                        <cell>لا نستطيع أن ندفع الأجرة.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell rend="tdLeft">ability</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdCom"/>
                        <cell rend="tdCentre">Can you (~do you know how to) play chess/domino? –
                            Yes.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdRight">
                            <hi rend="red">ǝtgidd-ǝš</hi> / tiʿrif-ǝš talʿab iš-šaṭṛanž / id-dīmīnu? –
                            ayh, ǝngidd / niʿrif.</cell>
                        <cell rend="tdID">Kannst du Schqubba spielen? – Ja.</cell>
